protocol.description:
Evaluation_Test_Type: Interval: At Minimum
Forecast_Test_Type: EvaluationNot recommended: series complete
General_Description: This test case describes when a child is administered the third dose of the HPV vaccine at 12 weeks from dose number 2 and at least 16 weeks - 4 days from dose number one, that the dose is considered to be valid.  The series is complete. (Prior to 12/16/16, 16 weeks - 4 days was allowed to be used as an Absolute Minimum Interval from Target Dose #1, and 12 weeks -4 days was allowed to be used as an Absolute Minimum Interval from Target Dose #2).
